OL,6,F"There are lots of vulnerable
OL,7,Fhouseholds who are being asked to pay
OL,8,Famounts of money that they simply
OL,9,Fcan't afford. We'd ask for a few
OL,10,Fthings. One, the councils start
OL,11,Fengaging as early as possible when
OL,12,Fthey see signs of financial distress
OL,13,Famongst their residents. Secondly, we
OL,14,Fneed to see council tax support
OL,15,Fpayments being put in place more
OL,16,Feffectively, and that is central
OL,17,Fgovernment funding being made
OL,18,Favailable for councils to do that." -
OL,19,FRICHARD LANE - Chief Client Officer,
OL,20,FStepChange Debt Charity
